1. Open Server Manager, click Tools, then open Group Policy Management.
2. Expand your domain and right-click Group Policy Objects > New.
3. Name the GPO Account Lockout, then click OK.
4. Right-click Account Lockout and select Edit to open the Group Policy Management Editor.
5. Navigate to:
Computer Configuration > Policies > Windows Settings > Security Settings > Account Policies > Account Lockout Policy
6. Configure the following settings:
-Account lockout threshold: Set to 10 invalid logon attempts
-Account lockout duration: Set to 15 minutes
-Reset account lockout counter after: Set to 15 minutes
7. Click Apply, then OK for each setting.
8. Close the Group Policy Management Editor.
9. Back in Group Policy Management, link the Account Lockout GPO to the GC Computers OU.
